{
  "id": 114669,
  "name": "Firefox Reader: custom width + multi column",
  "description": "Firefox has the new reader mode (about:reader) to facilitate reading of (almost) any article in a simple, pleasant, constant style. However, the width of the article view is remarkably thin for a single column. Meh... change.\r\nThis styles allows to customize the width of the view but also to use a layout with more than a single column, making it more akin to a newspaper.\r\n\r\nThe image shows the 5-column view on a display with 2560px width.",
